{{#> layout
  title='Grammar checker for English, German, French, and other languages'
  metaDescription='Perfect your writing with an AI grammar checker that explains errors. Master English, German, French, and more with real-time, educational corrections.'
  url='/grammar.html'
  ogDescription='Perfect your writing with an AI grammar checker that explains errors. Master English, German, French, and more with real-time, educational corrections.'
  navbarAlwaysMurky=true
  navbarClass="mb-4"
  navbarContainerClass="container-md"
  noCta=true
  hidePricing=true
  nonStickyNavbar=true
}}
  <div class="container-md" style="min-height: 30vh;">
    <div id="grammar-checker" class="pt-3 pb-5"></div>
  </div>
  <div style="background: #f9f9f9;">
    <div class="container-md py-5" style="font-size: 80%">
      <h1 class="h5" style="color: var(--bs-body-color); font-size: 140%">AI grammar checker and corrector</h1>
      <div class="mb-4">
        The philosophy of Vocably is to enable and encourage people to use language in real life in order to become fluent. Active production—speaking and writing—is the fastest catalyst for linguistic growth.
      </div>
      <div class="mb-4">
        However, it is not always possible to have a teacher who can correct every sentence. For that, Vocably provides a free AI grammar corrector designed to act as a personal linguistic coach. This tool not only corrects mistakes but also explains the reasoning behind corrections, helping learners understand the "why" so they can avoid the same errors in the future.
      </div>
      <div>
        This approach promotes a "production-first" mindset: before reaching for Google Translate or any other automatic translator, try to write the thought in the target language as best as possible. Engaging the brain to bridge the gap between thoughts and words is a powerful cognitive exercise. By attempting to express ideas independently before seeking AI assistance, users will see a significant impact on their overall language progress.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
{{/layout}}

